# OpenCut - Future Roadmap & Vision

## Our Vision
To create the most powerful, user-friendly, and feature-rich open-source video editing solution that empowers creators worldwide.

## Core Development Priorities

### Phase 1: Foundation (Q3 2025)
- [ ] Core video editing engine optimization
- [ ] Multi-format support (MP4, MOV, AVI, WebM)
- [ ] Basic transitions system
- [ ] Timeline improvements
- [ ] Project auto-save
- [ ] Performance optimization for HD/4K content

### Phase 2: Advanced Features (Q4 2025)
- [ ] GPU acceleration support
- [ ] Advanced layer system
- [ ] Custom effects engine
- [ ] Audio editing tools
- [ ] Text animation system
- [ ] Scene detection
- [ ] Video stabilization

### Phase 3: AI Integration (Q1 2026)
- [ ] Smart video enhancement
- [ ] Automatic subtitle generation
- [ ] Content-aware scaling
- [ ] Smart scene suggestions
- [ ] Background removal
- [ ] Audio enhancement

## Feature Roadmap

### Video Editing
- Advanced timeline management
- Multiple video tracks
- Keyframe animation
- Motion tracking
- Color grading tools
- Speed ramping
- Masking tools

### Audio
- Multi-track audio editing
- Audio effects library
- Voice-over recording
- Audio visualization
- Background noise removal
- Audio sync features

### Effects & Transitions
- Custom transition editor
- Effects library
- Real-time preview
- Particle system
- Green screen effects
- LUT support

### Export & Share
- Multiple export formats
- Social media presets
- Custom export settings
- Batch export
- Direct social media sharing
- Cloud backup integration

## Technical Improvements

### Performance
- Modular architecture
- Cache system optimization
- Memory management
- Preview rendering optimization
- Background processing

### Cross-Platform
- Windows optimization
- macOS support
- Linux compatibility
- Mobile export options

## Community Features

### Templates & Assets
- Community template gallery
- Asset sharing system
- Effect preset sharing
- Custom plugin support
- Resource library

### Collaboration
- Project sharing
- Team features
- Version control
- Comments and feedback system

## How to Contribute
We welcome contributions in various forms:
- Code contributions
- Feature suggestions
- Bug reports
- Documentation
- Translations
- Testing
- Design improvements

## Priority Goals
1. Performance and stability
2. User-friendly interface
3. Professional-grade features
4. Community-driven development
5. Cross-platform compatibility

## Long-term Vision
- Become the industry standard for open-source video editing
- Build a strong, active community
- Maintain high-quality documentation
- Regular release cycles
- Continuous integration of modern technologies

---

Note: This roadmap is dynamic and will be updated based on community feedback and technological advancements. All contributions, whether big or small, are valuable to the project's success.

For detailed technical specifications and implementation discussions, please refer to individual issues in our GitHub repository.
